  "texts": [
    "Lahza et al. (2023) trained CNN on eye images and videos,Figure 4.",
    "Anatomical and biological sites assessed by deep aging clocks (DACs) to estimate biological age.",
    "The brackets indicate the number of DACs reviewed for each category.Lee et al. (2022) developed 3D-DenseNet models trained on feed-forward CNNs to predict brain age in healthy individuals [78].",
    "The training dataset included Fluorodeoxyglucose Positron Emission Tomography (FDG PET) and Magnetic Resonance Images (MRI) brain scans of dementia patients and cognitively unimpaired controls.",
    "The clock performed with MAE of 3.14 years in predicting brain age when trained on FDG PET scans and MAE of 3.51 years when trained on MRI scans."
  ]
}